Get Parameters by Configuration Group

Source: R/core_parameter_registry.R
get_params_by_group.Rd

Retrieves all parameters belonging to a specific configuration group, optionally filtered by model type.

Usage

get_params_by_group(config_group, model_type = NULL)

Arguments

config_group

Character. Configuration group: "llm_args", "output_args", "interpretation_args"

model_type

Character or NULL. Model type filter: "fa", "gm", "irt", "cdm" (only applies to interpretation_args)

Value

Named list of parameter metadata

Examples

# Get all LLM parameters
get_params_by_group("llm_args")
